The Yobe State Committee on the Prevention and Control of Coronavirus led by the deputy governor, Idi Barde Gubana (Wazirin Fune), has embarked on mass fumigation and disinfection of ministries, agencies, places of worship and markets across the 17 local government areas of the state. Flagging-off the exercise in Damaturu, Gubana said although, Yobe did not record any confirmed case of Coronavirus, the disinfection was part of measures by the Buni administration towards curtailing the spread of the virus among other diseases in the state. “Hon. Mai Mala Buni has directed  the immediate fumigation of the entire state including markets, mosques and churches against COVID-19 and other related diseases. So far we have not recorded any confirm case of corona virus in our state and people of Yobe State are prayerful,” Gubana said. The deputy governor also commended people of the state for adhering to the norms of self-hygiene as well as observance of social distancing, adding that the COVID-19 committee is determined to ensure that people of the state are protected. The commissioner for Environment, Alhaji Sidi Yakubu Karasuwa, who is also the member of the committee said a total of 27 fire fighting vehicles heaped with chlorine solution will be used in disinfecting the 17 local government areas of the state. Karasuwa said, “Your Excellency we are also using 300 sprayers across the state with the following distribution, Damaturu 20 sprayers, Potiskum 20 while the rest of the local government will having 15 sprayers each.” The commissioner revealed that a total of 582 personnel would be engaged in the disinfection exercise, 300 personnel personals for spraying, 82 supervision and 200 fire fighters to man vehicles among other equipment.